<subsection xml:id="subsec-construction-of-irregular-polygons">
        <title>Construction of irregular polygons</title>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                An irregular polygon does not have equal sides and equal angles. 
            </p>
        </introduction>

        <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-construction-of-irregular-triangle">
            <title>Construction of irregular triangles</title>
            <p>
               There are different types of irregular triangles namely: isosceles, scalene and right triangle.
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Properties of isoscles triangle.</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           Only two sides are equal in length. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           Opposite angles of the triangle are equal. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The sum of the angles add up to <m>180^\circ.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>

            <p>
                <term>Properties of scalene triangle.</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           All the three sides have different length. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           All the angles have different sizes. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The sum of the angles add up to <m>180^\circ.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>

            <p>
                <term>Properties of right triangle.</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           The sides are not equal in length. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           One of the angle measures  <m>90^\circ.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The sum of the angles add up to <m>180^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            
